[[File:Degg's Model.png|thumb|348x348px|Degg's Model]]The '''Degg's Model''' shows that a disaster only occurs if a vulnerable population is exposed to a [[hazard]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=yT09CgAAQBAJ&pg=PT45&q=Degg's%20model|title=Edexcel A level Geography Book 1 Third Edition|last=Dunn|first=Cameron|publisher=Hodder Education|year=2016|pages=Chapter 2, Page 2}}</ref>  It was devised in 1992 by Dr. [[Martin Degg]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.chester.ac.uk/departments/geography-and-development-studies/staff/martin-degg|title=Dr Martin Degg  {{!}} Geography and International Development {{!}} University Of Chester|website=www.chester.ac.uk|language=en|access-date=2017-12-21}}</ref> Head of Geography at the [[University of Chester]].

