'''Infrared cirrus''' are filamentary structures seen in space that emit [[infrared]] [[light]]. The name is given because the structures are [[cloud]]-like in appearance.<ref name=Low1984/> These structures were first detected by the [[IRAS|Infrared Astronomy Satellite]] at [[wavelength]]s of 60 and 100 [[micrometre]]s.
