'''Parahydrogen Induced Polarization''' (PHIP) is a technique used in [[magnetic resonance imaging]].  The technique relies on the incorporation of hyperpolarized H<sub>2</sub> into molecules, usually by [[hydrogenation]].<ref>{{cite journal|journal=Progress in Nuclear Magnetic Resonance Spectroscopy|volume=67|year=2012|pages=1–48|title=The theory and practice of hyperpolarization in magnetic resonance using parahydrogen|authors=Richard A.Green, Ralph W.Adams, Simon B.Duckett, Ryan E.Mewis, David C.Williamson, Gary G.R.Green|doi=10.1016/j.pnmrs.2012.03.001}}</ref>

